The paper deals with an online allocation problem with stochastic durations, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem involves making decisions based on incomplete information, which is a common theme in data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new framework for analyzing competitiveness, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
